  "description": "Growing protocol for *Valerianella locusta* (mâche, lamb's lettuce), exceptionally frost-hardy winter salad green. Seed exhibits thermodormancy above 68°F; sow only in fall (late August through September). Hardy to 5–10°F; matures in 60–90 days under cool conditions. Winter through early spring harvest in temperate climates.",
